1
00:00:38,233 --> 00:00:39,367
<i> Andrea!</i>

2
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:41,433
<i>You cannot stay here!
Is that so hard to understand?</i>

3
00:00:41,567 --> 00:00:43,367
<i> You are so hard-headed!</i>

4
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:45,667
<i>Mom, are you going
to the hospital?</i>

5
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:47,000
<i> Yes!</i>

6
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:49,700
<i>If she wants to fight, she'd
better face me! Not my children!</i>

7
00:00:49,833 --> 00:00:51,933
<i>We have the right
to see my father!</i>

8
00:00:52,067 --> 00:00:53,567
<i> You piss me off!</i>

9
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:54,767
<i> Sis!</i>

10
00:00:57,267 --> 00:00:58,433
<i> Mom!</i>

11
00:00:58,567 --> 00:01:01,767
<i>One of your nurses pushed
my daughter down the stairs!</i>

12
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:03,100
<i> She's your employee!</i>

13
00:01:03,233 --> 00:01:04,367
<i> You have to fire her!</i>

14
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:06,467
<i>If not, I will file
a case against her...</i>

15
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:07,933
<i> And this hospital!</i>

16
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:09,600
<i>If this hospital
gets in trouble</i>

17
00:01:09,733 --> 00:01:12,667
<i>because of your bad behavior,
I will fire you!</i>

18
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:13,967
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

19
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:16,167
<i>I did not intend to push
your daughter down the stairs.</i>

20
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:18,333
<i>I now allow you
to see Manuel.</i>

21
00:01:18,467 --> 00:01:21,033
<i>But you have to clean
my name to my boss!</i>

22
00:01:21,167 --> 00:01:23,133
<i> I acknowledge that Hazel</i>

23
00:01:23,267 --> 00:01:25,133
<i>accidentally pushed
my daughter down the stairs.</i>

24
00:01:25,267 --> 00:01:26,733
<i> I will no longer file a case.</i>

25
00:01:26,867 --> 00:01:28,400
<i> Manuel, please do not give up.</i>

26
00:01:28,533 --> 00:01:30,933
<i>You still have to patch
things up with Andrea.</i>

27
00:01:31,067 --> 00:01:32,000
<i> And also Jeff.</i>

28
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:34,767
<i>You still have to keep
your promises to me.</i>

29
00:01:35,433 --> 00:01:38,133
<i>"I will take care of
myself, Felma."</i>

30
00:01:38,267 --> 00:01:44,533
<i>"I will do everything
just to walk again..."</i>

31
00:01:46,933 --> 00:01:56,900
<i>"And to walk you down the aisle
without using a wheelchair."</i>

32
00:01:57,733 --> 00:02:02,567
<i> To marry you, that's my dream.</i>

33
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:04,333
<i> Oh no, that's just an expense.</i>

34
00:02:04,467 --> 00:02:07,300
<i>It does not have to be grand.
Even a modest one will do.</i>

35
00:02:07,433 --> 00:02:10,067
<i> I just want to marry you.</i>

36
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:13,833
<i>Love, we have talked about
the wedding a few times.</i>

37
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,567
<i>Let's just take care
of the kids first.</i>

38
00:02:16,700 --> 00:02:20,267
<i>They are my priority, that's why
I want us to get married.</i>

39
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:24,333
<i>I want this union and our
family to be blessed by God.</i>

40
00:02:24,467 --> 00:02:28,800
<i>I really hope that my marriage
to Hazel will be annulled soon,</i>

41
00:02:28,933 --> 00:02:31,033
<i> so I can marry you.</i>

42
00:02:31,167 --> 00:02:34,533
<i>I want that whole world to
know how much I love you.</i>

43
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:42,900
I will wait until the day you
get to keep your promises to me.

44
00:02:43,567 --> 00:02:45,300
When you wake up,

45
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:49,867
please get well soon.

46
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:53,400
You have to take good
care of yourself.

47
00:02:54,600 --> 00:03:00,767
So you can process the annulment
papers immediately.

48
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,900
I have to admit...

49
00:03:10,667 --> 00:03:13,600
This is the only missing piece.

50
00:03:13,733 --> 00:03:17,233
Then I will be able
to love you fully again.

51
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:27,233
And right at this moment, I will
fight for my love for you.

52
00:03:33,367 --> 00:03:35,133
I will take you back...

53
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:40,033
from the woman
who took you away from me.

54
00:03:52,167 --> 00:03:54,300
I will take you back, Manuel.

55
00:03:55,767 --> 00:03:57,533
I will take you back.

56
00:04:08,267 --> 00:04:10,467
That Felma is such
a pain in the ass.

57
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:13,100
I saw her whispering
things to my husband.

58
00:04:13,233 --> 00:04:15,067
She's got the upper hand,
friend.

59
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:18,267
So the lawsuit
was just her leverage.

60
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:20,433
That's your fault, Mom.

61
00:04:20,567 --> 00:04:25,000
You didn't control yourself.
You hurt Andrea!

62
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:29,300
Really?
You call her your big sister?

63
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:31,000
Why?

64
00:04:31,667 --> 00:04:33,400
Are you on her side now?

65
00:04:33,833 --> 00:04:38,000
You are not even
related to her!

66
00:04:39,100 --> 00:04:40,600
If I hear that from you
one more time,

67
00:04:40,733 --> 00:04:42,833
I will tell her
who you really are!

68
00:04:42,967 --> 00:04:45,000
Mom, stop reminding
me about it, please!

69
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:46,367
Then stop calling her
big sister!

70
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:47,967
Hey, hey, hey.

71
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:49,433
Stop it.

72
00:04:49,567 --> 00:04:51,533
Do not fight with each other.

73
00:04:53,033 --> 00:04:57,200
So, Felma gained
access to Manuel?

74
00:04:57,333 --> 00:04:58,900
What are you going to do?

75
00:04:59,567 --> 00:05:01,433
Cut the access.

76
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:04,133
But Mom, you had an agreement.

77
00:05:04,267 --> 00:05:06,100
I just gave what Miles wants.

78
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:12,467
But that would be the last
time Felma could be near Manuel.

79
00:05:13,233 --> 00:05:17,600
That would be your task now,
when I'm not around.

80
00:05:17,733 --> 00:05:18,867
You have to keep an eye on
Manuel and make sure that

81
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,633
Felma won't have
access to him.

82
00:05:20,767 --> 00:05:22,233
Block her way if you have to!

83
00:05:22,367 --> 00:05:25,067
- But Mom...
- Jessica...

84
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:26,767
Don't even try to argue.

85
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:29,833
Your mom's decisions
are always final.

86
00:05:30,767 --> 00:05:33,367
Finish your meal.

87
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:36,800
And after that, you can go rest.

88
00:05:36,967 --> 00:05:39,200
Tomorrow,
I will give you a task.

89
00:05:48,133 --> 00:05:49,133
Mom...

90
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:53,200
I told you I would go
with you to the hospital.

91
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:56,200
You're the only
one who saw Dad.

92
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:57,500
That's fine.

93
00:05:58,133 --> 00:05:59,767
We were not able to come close.

94
00:06:00,567 --> 00:06:02,033
But maybe later.

95
00:06:02,167 --> 00:06:04,533
You have to take me with you!

96
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:06,933
Are you ready to see Jessica?

97
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:11,400
Speaking of Jessica...

98
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:18,067
Can we please talk about what
happened between the two of you?

99
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,700
I thought you were close to her?
What happened?

100
00:06:24,733 --> 00:06:28,133
You did not know.
Those two always fight.

101
00:06:28,267 --> 00:06:30,567
They even went into
a physical fight.

102
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:33,167
And Hazel even confronted me.

103
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:34,900
Sweetie, come on.

104
00:06:35,033 --> 00:06:36,867
Tell us.

105
00:06:38,267 --> 00:06:40,167
That's nothing, Mom.

106
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:42,300
Just petty
sisterly fights.

107
00:06:42,867 --> 00:06:48,000
I would also have to admit that
sometimes, I start the fight.

108
00:06:48,133 --> 00:06:50,333
But we will patch things up.

109
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:53,200
I will be the one
to say sorry first.

110
00:06:54,033 --> 00:06:56,967
I don't want us to fight,
anyway.

111
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,033
I miss how we used to be.

112
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:04,167
Just be sure about that, okay?

113
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:05,800
Yes, Mom.

114
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:09,767
Sis, how was your first
encounter with Hazel?

115
00:07:10,933 --> 00:07:13,300
Our big brother was right.

116
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:15,400
Look at what she did to me, Mom.

117
00:07:15,567 --> 00:07:17,400
I cannot even eat normally.

118
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:22,967
She really is Satan's sister!
She is so evil!

119
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:26,167
She was able to push me
like that with her small built!

120
00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:28,133
Size doesn't really
matter if you are evil.

121
00:07:28,267 --> 00:07:31,167
If you have a bad attitude,
it is what it is.

122
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:33,200
I feel bad for Jessica.

123
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:37,633
Of all the moms she could've
had, it had to be Hazel.

124
00:07:37,767 --> 00:07:39,933
Good thing she takes after Dad.

125
00:07:40,067 --> 00:07:41,467
She is kind.

126
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:43,533
We're not sure.

127
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:47,767
What do you mean, Coleen?

128
00:07:50,433 --> 00:07:51,633
Andrea, please
pass the cheese.

129
00:07:51,767 --> 00:07:53,033
I got it.

130
00:07:53,167 --> 00:07:54,367
Here's your cheese.

131
00:07:55,167 --> 00:07:56,100
Thank you.

132
00:07:56,767 --> 00:07:59,067
Jessica,
I didn't notice you there.

133
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:02,800
Jessica, dear, you did not
inform us that you'd be coming.

134
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:05,467
Come and join us. Let's eat.

135
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,600
Thank you, Aunt Felma.

136
00:08:07,733 --> 00:08:10,200
I already ate at the hospital.

137
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:12,467
I just need to get
something from my room.

138
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:16,167
Dad's papers for the insurance.

139
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:18,567
- Okay, sweetheart.
- Excuse me.

140
00:08:24,867 --> 00:08:26,133
Coleen,

141
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:31,600
this is your chance
to talk to your sister.

142
00:08:31,733 --> 00:08:32,900
Go.

143
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:36,600
You said you would
apologize first.

144
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:55,100
Jessica...

145
00:08:56,567 --> 00:08:57,633
What's that?

146
00:08:57,767 --> 00:09:00,700
I thought you would
only get Dad's papers?

147
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:03,133
Why are you getting
all of his stuff?

148
00:09:03,267 --> 00:09:04,933
Because as soon as Dad
gets discharged,

149
00:09:05,067 --> 00:09:06,933
we will move
into a new apartment.

150
00:09:07,067 --> 00:09:07,600
What?

151
00:09:08,533 --> 00:09:10,267
Said who?

152
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:11,800
Your mom?

153
00:09:11,933 --> 00:09:12,767
No.

154
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:13,967
I did.

155
00:09:15,433 --> 00:09:16,900
You would take him away from us?

156
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:19,267
You want to be
the only one around him?

157
00:09:20,967 --> 00:09:22,867
And now the truth came out.

158
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:24,867
And I am right.

159
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:26,867
You really take after your mom.

160
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:30,033
You're just as mean as she is!

161
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:35,633
You are worse than me, Coleen!
You always hurt me!

162
00:09:35,767 --> 00:09:37,700
You always pick fights with me!

163
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:38,700
How about you?

164
00:09:38,833 --> 00:09:40,367
Where did you get that
kind of attitude?

165
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:43,600
I'm sure not from Dad
because he is kind-hearted.

166
00:09:43,733 --> 00:09:48,333
And definitely not from Aunt
Felma, as she is also kind.

167
00:09:48,933 --> 00:09:50,667
So...

168
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:53,600
Where did that bad
attitude come from?

169
00:09:53,733 --> 00:09:56,867
Try hurting me once again!
Do your worst, Coleen!

170
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,167
Because it will be your last!

171
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:00,767
I will fight for my rights

172
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:03,900
as my dad's legal daughter
from now on, Coleen!

173
00:10:04,067 --> 00:10:07,600
I will not allow you to visit
Dad or even come close to him!

174
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:12,267
You always accuse me
of being my mom's ally

175
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,667
in everything that she does.

176
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:15,667
Even when none of those
prove to be true.

177
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:19,400
And if that's what you think,
then let's make it our truth!

178
00:10:19,533 --> 00:10:21,667
I'll tell her to fight
harder to get rid of all of you

179
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:25,033
and banish you from Dad's life!

180
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:28,667
No. I will not allow
that to happen.

181
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,600
We'll see about that.

182
00:10:32,833 --> 00:10:34,733
Why are you doing this to us?

183
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:36,700
Because you started it!

184
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:40,467
You pushed me away, Coleen.

185
00:10:41,533 --> 00:10:43,800
You made me an enemy.

186
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:47,967
So let me ask you
the same question...

187
00:10:49,433 --> 00:10:51,900
Why did you do
those things to me?

188
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:58,467
Because I was jealous!

189
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:01,800
Because I envy you!

190
00:11:05,767 --> 00:11:08,800
Darling, give this to Joel.

191
00:11:09,467 --> 00:11:13,900
Tell him I thank him for all the
help that he extended to you.

192
00:11:14,033 --> 00:11:16,467
Thank you, Mom.

193
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:20,133
This is too much!
He cannot finish all this.

194
00:11:20,267 --> 00:11:23,100
He still has an IV
attached to him.

195
00:11:23,233 --> 00:11:25,167
Just stay here
for a little while.

196
00:11:25,300 --> 00:11:27,267
I will take you home later.

197
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,933
I want to extend
our bonding moment.

198
00:11:29,067 --> 00:11:31,167
Let me take you home.

199
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:33,100
Yes, darling.

200
00:11:33,233 --> 00:11:36,133
It has been a while since
we had this moment.

201
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:41,733
I can't, Mom. Brix, the one
who's looking after Joel now,

202
00:11:41,900 --> 00:11:43,467
has to go to work.

203
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:47,233
If I do not come now,
no one will look after Joel.

204
00:11:47,767 --> 00:11:50,800
I understand. You have to take
good care of Joel.

205
00:11:50,933 --> 00:11:55,867
Where's Jessica, Mom? I think we
can go to the hospital together.

206
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,867
That's a good idea.
You should go together.

207
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,200
I will walk you to the door.

208
00:12:01,267 --> 00:12:02,767
Take care.

209
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:03,733
Thank you, Didang.

210
00:12:03,867 --> 00:12:05,467
I'm hungry.

211
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,000
Do we still have food left?

212
00:12:07,967 --> 00:12:09,467
Jealous?

213
00:12:09,933 --> 00:12:11,600
Why?

214
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:15,133
You were with Dad all your life.

215
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:17,267
But me?

216
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:21,700
I just got to be with him now!
And you're taking him away?

217
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:25,067
Why do you want him
to leave us again?

218
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:29,333
Because I am scared that you
will take my dad away from me!

219
00:12:29,467 --> 00:12:31,967
That will never happen!

220
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:35,067
Really, Coleen? You will not
take him away?

221
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:37,200
Don't make things up, Jessica!

222
00:12:37,333 --> 00:12:38,167
Liar!

223
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,333
I saw in Mom's hidden cam

224
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:44,033
that you and your brother
were talking to each other!

225
00:12:44,167 --> 00:12:48,633
And don't you dare deny it,
because I saved a copy!

226
00:12:54,633 --> 00:12:56,500
This will always remind me

227
00:12:56,633 --> 00:12:58,933
that you want to take
my dad away from me!

228
00:12:59,067 --> 00:13:01,133
<i> Dad went away again.</i>

229
00:13:01,933 --> 00:13:03,733
<i> This is all Jessica's fault.</i>

230
00:13:03,867 --> 00:13:06,333
<i> She always gets in the way!</i>

231
00:13:06,467 --> 00:13:07,767
<i>She's not even a part
of this family.</i>

232
00:13:07,900 --> 00:13:09,133
<i>But she always wants
to get involved.</i>

233
00:13:09,267 --> 00:13:10,800
<i> I thought you were close?</i>

234
00:13:10,933 --> 00:13:14,100
<i>We used to be.
But things got out of hand.</i>

235
00:13:14,233 --> 00:13:15,900
<i>She's getting Mom's
attention, too.</i>

236
00:13:16,033 --> 00:13:17,800
<i>She's just never satisfied
with what she has.</i>

237
00:13:17,933 --> 00:13:19,133
<i>She used to get all
of Dad's attention.</i>

238
00:13:19,267 --> 00:13:22,167
<i>- And now, even Mom's!
-That wasn't the only time...</i>

239
00:13:22,333 --> 00:13:25,033
that you talked about me,
Coleen.

240
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:27,767
<i>What will happen when
Dad's marriage to Hazel</i>

241
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:29,300
<i> is finally annulled?</i>

242
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:34,067
<i>I hope that Dad
and Mom get back together.</i>

243
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:36,067
<i> But how about Jessica?</i>

244
00:13:37,833 --> 00:13:39,033
<i> I don't know.</i>

245
00:13:39,167 --> 00:13:42,133
<i>She should go with her mom.
Anyway, that's her real mom.</i>

246
00:13:42,267 --> 00:13:43,500
<i> And not our mom.</i>

247
00:13:43,633 --> 00:13:46,533
<i> She has to go back to her mom.</i>

248
00:13:46,667 --> 00:13:47,800
<i> I have the same thoughts.</i>

249
00:13:47,933 --> 00:13:51,567
<i>I wouldn't mind
if she visits Dad.</i>

250
00:13:51,700 --> 00:13:54,867
<i>But I don't want her to
be a part of our family.</i>

251
00:13:55,033 --> 00:13:59,233
I will not squeeze
myself into this family.

252
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:04,767
But I'll make sure that
you will not have my dad back!

253
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:06,600
And what will you do?

254
00:14:06,733 --> 00:14:09,500
You will block their
annulment plans?

255
00:14:12,267 --> 00:14:13,333
You're a monster!

256
00:14:18,533 --> 00:14:19,300
Coleen?

257
00:14:20,133 --> 00:14:20,933
Hey, wait!

258
00:14:21,567 --> 00:14:22,667
That's enough!

259
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,600
- That's enough!
- Coleen!

260
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:29,067
Coleen, you're hurting
Jessica again!

261
00:14:29,233 --> 00:14:32,267
What's happening to you, Coleen?

262
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:35,367
She's trying to take
Dad away from us!

263
00:14:36,567 --> 00:14:39,367
She will block the marriage
annulment of Dad to her mom!

264
00:14:42,033 --> 00:14:43,000
What are you talking about,
Coleen?

265
00:14:43,133 --> 00:14:45,967
Wait! Wait! Annulment?

266
00:14:47,033 --> 00:14:48,700
What annulment?

267
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:51,333
Yes!

268
00:14:51,467 --> 00:14:53,900
She will block the annulment

269
00:14:54,033 --> 00:14:56,200
so they can all be together
without us!

270
00:14:56,333 --> 00:14:59,800
Don't lie, Coleen!
I never said that!

271
00:14:59,933 --> 00:15:00,567
What?

272
00:15:00,700 --> 00:15:03,033
- Enough!
- Coleen, enough!

273
00:15:04,767 --> 00:15:08,733
Andrea, take Jessica
with you when you go.

274
00:15:13,700 --> 00:15:14,967
I am telling the truth.

275
00:15:15,100 --> 00:15:16,400
Enough.

276
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,833
Go now, Jessica. Go, Andrea.

277
00:15:20,967 --> 00:15:22,767
- Hey, hey, enough.
- Coleen, enough.

278
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:25,700
Enough!

279
00:15:25,833 --> 00:15:27,167
We need to talk.

280
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:28,167
Come here!

281
00:15:28,967 --> 00:15:30,433
Let us talk.

282
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:50,367
On behalf of Coleen,
I apologize.

283
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:55,167
Do you want to
talk about it?

284
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:01,933
Are you going
to the hospital, too?

285
00:16:02,867 --> 00:16:05,633
You can come with me.
My ride is on the way.

286
00:16:05,767 --> 00:16:07,900
No thanks, Andrea.

287
00:16:09,833 --> 00:16:11,000
I'm sorry.

288
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:18,367
It's fine, Jessica.

289
00:16:19,833 --> 00:16:21,767
Besides, I am your big sister.

290
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,467
<i>If I hear that from you
one more time,</i>

291
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:30,400
<i>I will tell her
who you really are!</i>

292
00:16:31,667 --> 00:16:32,933
Are you good?

293
00:16:45,833 --> 00:16:49,133
Don't play the victim, Coleen.
We saw what you did.

294
00:16:49,267 --> 00:16:51,033
You were hurting Jessica.

295
00:16:51,167 --> 00:16:54,300
Because she wants
to stop the annulment!

296
00:16:54,433 --> 00:16:57,333
Why don't you want
to believe me?

297
00:16:57,467 --> 00:16:58,667
Why should we believe you?

298
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:00,733
You said she did
not say a thing.

299
00:17:00,867 --> 00:17:02,667
She smiled!

300
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:05,100
She meant yes!

301
00:17:05,233 --> 00:17:06,867
Stop assuming.

302
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:08,433
Fine!

303
00:17:09,100 --> 00:17:11,633
Take Jessica's side!

304
00:17:11,767 --> 00:17:14,333
We are not taking her side.

305
00:17:15,533 --> 00:17:17,600
We just do not want you
to make up stories

306
00:17:17,733 --> 00:17:19,633
to ruin Jessica's image.

307
00:17:19,767 --> 00:17:23,467
Mom, I am not making up stories!

308
00:17:26,567 --> 00:17:30,567
She is supporting
her dad's decision.

309
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:33,067
I talked to Manuel.

310
00:17:34,033 --> 00:17:37,167
So please stop
fighting with Jessica.

311
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:38,933
She is still your sister.

312
00:17:39,067 --> 00:17:40,933
She is your youngest sister.

313
00:17:41,067 --> 00:17:43,067
You have to act like
a big sister to her!

314
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:53,600
Hazel agreed that
we can visit your dad.

315
00:17:54,267 --> 00:17:57,867
If she knew about what you
did to her daughter,

316
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,500
I'm sure she would take her
decision back!

317
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:03,933
Do you want to see
your dad or not?

318
00:18:04,067 --> 00:18:05,467
I want to see him.

319
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,133
Is that so?

320
00:18:07,267 --> 00:18:08,933
Then you have to behave.

321
00:18:18,700 --> 00:18:20,467
Calm down.

322
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,000
Stop crying.

323
00:18:22,733 --> 00:18:25,400
Hazel and I have been fighting.

324
00:18:25,533 --> 00:18:29,967
I do not want the same to
happen between you and Jessica.

325
00:18:55,733 --> 00:18:57,167
There you go.

326
00:19:00,733 --> 00:19:04,767
You have to try
Mom's longganisa.

327
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:07,200
Wow!

328
00:19:07,933 --> 00:19:09,967
Afritada!

329
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:11,733
You brought a lot of food.

330
00:19:11,867 --> 00:19:13,433
Your mom spoils me a lot.

331
00:19:13,567 --> 00:19:16,967
She said she's thankful
for all your help.

332
00:19:17,100 --> 00:19:22,000
How's your hand, by the way?

333
00:19:22,133 --> 00:19:23,900
It's better now.

334
00:19:24,033 --> 00:19:27,733
It still hurts
a bit sometimes.

335
00:19:28,533 --> 00:19:30,200
Take a bite.

336
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:34,667
Here we go.

337
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:51,133
Your mom's dishes are the best!
Tastes so good!

338
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:56,500
She actually wants to meet you.

339
00:19:57,533 --> 00:20:01,067
She wants to thank
you personally.

340
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:05,133
Not here in the hospital. I want
our first meeting to be special.

341
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:07,867
Of course! She wants that, too.

342
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,067
She actually wants to
invite you to our home.

343
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:11,800
So she can cook
a special meal for you.

344
00:20:11,933 --> 00:20:15,133
Wow, she really likes me.

345
00:20:15,267 --> 00:20:18,000
Maybe if I ask for your hand
to be my girlfriend,

346
00:20:18,133 --> 00:20:19,467
she will say yes.

347
00:20:20,667 --> 00:20:22,567
Stop that!

348
00:20:23,367 --> 00:20:24,633
Why?

349
00:20:24,767 --> 00:20:27,700
Your wound is on the other side.
I hit you on this side!

350
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,567
You hit my heart.

351
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:32,967
Don't you want me to court you?

352
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:36,500
I will hit you again! Stop that!

353
00:20:36,667 --> 00:20:38,067
Here, eat some more.

354
00:20:40,167 --> 00:20:41,700
But seriously...

355
00:20:42,733 --> 00:20:45,967
Can I court you?

356
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:48,900
Hold on.

357
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:51,400
Hello?

358
00:20:52,100 --> 00:20:53,200
What?

359
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:54,133
Right now?

360
00:20:54,267 --> 00:20:56,167
I thought this was scheduled
later?

361
00:20:56,300 --> 00:20:58,500
All right. I'm coming.

362
00:20:58,633 --> 00:21:00,767
Thank you, Jessica. Thank you!

363
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:02,067
I will come back, Joel.

364
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:04,000
- What happened?
- I will come back.

365
00:21:05,133 --> 00:21:06,433
Laters!

366
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:21,633
Jessica allowed me
to come in, Dad.

367
00:21:21,767 --> 00:21:23,733
I don't know why.

368
00:21:34,467 --> 00:21:37,933
<i>I'm doing this for you. I want
you to get well sooner.</i>

369
00:21:38,067 --> 00:21:41,333
<i> You said you would come home.</i>

370
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:43,700
<i> I miss you so much!</i>

371
00:21:44,533 --> 00:21:47,900
<i> I miss you, too.</i>

372
00:21:48,033 --> 00:21:51,133
<i>Your mom and your siblings, too.</i>

373
00:21:51,267 --> 00:21:54,100
<i> But Dad needs to work.</i>

374
00:22:03,567 --> 00:22:07,300
Mom, they only allow
two people in the ICU.

375
00:22:07,433 --> 00:22:09,267
Can my siblings just come
at the same time,

376
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:10,867
so I can come in alone?

377
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,133
No.

378
00:22:12,267 --> 00:22:13,733
We will come in together,
and Andrea will come in solo.

379
00:22:13,867 --> 00:22:16,467
Let's give Andrea a chance
to be alone with Dad.

380
00:22:16,633 --> 00:22:18,167
Let's go.

381
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:20,833
Mom, please! I want to be alone
with Dad, too.

382
00:22:20,967 --> 00:22:22,167
No.

383
00:22:22,300 --> 00:22:24,867
Jeff, please! I am the youngest!

384
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,333
Coleen, we already said no!

385
00:22:26,467 --> 00:22:28,100
Stop fighting over this.

386
00:22:28,233 --> 00:22:29,833
Listen to your big brother.

387
00:22:29,967 --> 00:22:30,900
Now, let's go.

388
00:22:31,033 --> 00:22:32,467
Listen to me.

389
00:23:20,567 --> 00:23:22,500
I'm sorry, Dad.

390
00:23:22,667 --> 00:23:25,233
I let myself be angry at you.

391
00:23:26,900 --> 00:23:31,933
I let the hurt
overpower everything.

392
00:23:33,667 --> 00:23:35,933
I closed my heart to you.

393
00:23:38,367 --> 00:23:40,900
I disrespected you...

394
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:44,767
and Mom.

395
00:23:48,633 --> 00:23:52,933
I hope you can still forgive me
for dishonoring you.

396
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,567
I'm sorry, Dad.

397
00:23:58,600 --> 00:24:00,633
I will make it up to you.

398
00:24:01,433 --> 00:24:04,267
I promise you that.

399
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:06,033
Please wake up, Dad.

400
00:24:07,167 --> 00:24:09,000
Please wake up.

401
00:24:09,133 --> 00:24:10,633
Please.

402
00:24:14,767 --> 00:24:15,967
Sorry.

403
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:20,200
I'm sorry, Dad.

404
00:24:24,367 --> 00:24:26,700
Please, wake up now.

405
00:24:29,100 --> 00:24:30,433
Daddy...

406
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,633
You ordered a lot.

407
00:24:46,767 --> 00:24:48,033
Are you that hungry?

408
00:24:48,167 --> 00:24:52,433
Food trip, Mom. The past few
days have been really stressful.

409
00:24:54,967 --> 00:24:58,133
Well. We haven't eaten well
recently.

410
00:25:02,567 --> 00:25:03,933
Here, Ma'am.

411
00:25:06,733 --> 00:25:09,433
Even this? Is this ours, too?

412
00:25:11,300 --> 00:25:12,833
What is this, Jessica?

413
00:25:12,967 --> 00:25:14,567
Mom, food trip!

414
00:25:18,300 --> 00:25:19,733
Food trip, Mom.

415
00:25:20,500 --> 00:25:21,933
What's your plan?

416
00:25:24,100 --> 00:25:25,567
What plan?

417
00:25:26,933 --> 00:25:27,900
I don't know.

418
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:33,600
Maybe you are delaying
our schedule at the ICU.

419
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:38,233
You don't want me to see
them visiting your Dad.

420
00:25:40,067 --> 00:25:42,300
You're being paranoid, Mom.

421
00:25:43,233 --> 00:25:44,533
Really?

422
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:47,067
We'll see about that.

423
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:48,600
Wait! Wait, Mom!

424
00:25:48,733 --> 00:25:51,333
- Get out of the way!
- Wait, Mom!

425
00:25:52,267 --> 00:25:52,833
Mom!

426
00:25:53,733 --> 00:25:55,000
<i> What are you doing?</i>

427
00:25:55,133 --> 00:25:55,900
<i> Isn't it obvious?</i>

428
00:25:56,033 --> 00:25:57,567
<i> Trying to stop you.</i>

429
00:25:57,700 --> 00:25:59,100
<i>So you won't be able
to see Manuel.</i>

430
00:25:59,233 --> 00:26:01,200
<i> Temporary restraining order.</i>

431
00:26:01,333 --> 00:26:03,767
<i>That evil Hazel
is really clever!</i>

432
00:26:03,900 --> 00:26:06,067
<i>How did she file
it that quickly?</i>

433
00:26:07,133 --> 00:26:08,167
<i> Mom...</i>

434
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:09,867
<i> Can I sleep here?</i>

435
00:26:10,033 --> 00:26:12,567
<i> Why are you here?</i>

436
00:26:13,833 --> 00:26:16,300
<i>What's happening?
Why are you all here?</i>

437
00:26:16,433 --> 00:26:19,367
<i>Don't we have any chance
left to visit our dad?</i>

438
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:20,800
<i> This can't be.</i>

439
00:26:20,933 --> 00:26:22,100
<i>I will be fine if they
treat me this way.</i>

440
00:26:22,233 --> 00:26:24,300
<i>But they shall never
touch you, my children!</i>

441
00:26:24,433 --> 00:26:28,433
<i>Tomorrow, you have to bring
your birth certificates.</i>

442
00:26:28,567 --> 00:26:33,233
<i>You have to show Hazel
your dad's signature!</i>

443
00:26:33,367 --> 00:26:35,333
<i> We will fight this, okay?</i>

444
00:26:35,467 --> 00:26:37,467
<i> We will fight!</i>
